{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:genesis.10",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "genesis",
    "chapterNumber": 10,
    "referenceLabel": "Genesis 10",
    "summary": "Source text for Genesis 10 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.10.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 10:1",
      "text": "These are the generations of the sons of Noah, Shem, Ham, and Japheth; sons were born to them after the flood.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.10.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 10:2",
      "text": "The sons of Japheth: Gomer, Magog, Madai, Javan, Tubal, Meshech, and Tiras.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.10.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 10:3",
      "text": "The sons of Gomer: Ashkenaz, Riphath, and Togarmah.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.10.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 10:4",
      "text": "The sons of Javan: Elishah, Tarshish, Kittim, and Dodanim.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.10.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 10:5",
      "text": "From these the coastland peoples spread. These are the sons of Japheth in their lands, each with his own language, by their families, in their nations.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.10.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 10:6",
      "text": "The sons of Ham: Cush, Egypt, Put, and Canaan.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.10.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 10:7",
      "text": "The sons of Cush: Seba, Havilah, Sabtah, Raamah, and Sabteca. The sons of Raamah: Sheba and Dedan.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.10.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 10:8",
      "text": "Cush became the father of Nimrod; he was the first on earth to be a mighty man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.10.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 10:9",
      "text": "He was a mighty hunter before the Lord; therefore it is said, “Like Nimrod a mighty hunter before the Lord.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.10.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 10:10",
      "text": "The beginning of his kingdom was Babel, Erech, and Accad, all of them in the land of Shinar.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.10.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 10:11",
      "text": "From that land he went into Assyria, and built Nineveh, Rehoboth-Ir, Calah, and",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.10.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 10:12",
      "text": "Resen between Nineveh and Calah; that is the great city.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.10.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 10:13",
      "text": "Egypt became the father of Ludim, Anamim, Lehabim, Naph-tuhim,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.10.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 10:14",
      "text": "Pathrusim, Casluhim (whence came the Philistines), and Caphtorim.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.10.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 10:15",
      "text": "Canaan became the father of Sidon his first-born, and Heth,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.10.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 10:16",
      "text": "and the Jebusites, the Amorites, the Girgashites,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.10.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 10:17",
      "text": "the Hivites, the Arkites, the Sinites,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.10.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 10:18",
      "text": "the Arvadites, the Zemarites, and the Hamathites. Afterward the families of the Canaanites spread abroad.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.10.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 10:19",
      "text": "And the territory of the Canaanites extended from Sidon, in the direction of Gerar, as far as Gaza, and in the direction of Sodom, Gomorrah, Admah, and Zeboiim, as far as Lasha.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.10.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 10:20",
      "text": "These are the sons of Ham, by their families, their languages, their lands, and their nations.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.10.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 10:21",
      "text": "To Shem also, the father of all the children of Eber, the elder brother of Japheth, children were born.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.10.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 10:22",
      "text": "The sons of Shem: Elam, Asshur, Arpachshad, Lud, and Aram.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.10.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 10:23",
      "text": "The sons of Aram: Uz, Hul, Gether, and Mash.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.10.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 10:24",
      "text": "Arpachshad became the father of Shelah; and Shelah became the father of Eber.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.10.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 10:25",
      "text": "To Eber were born two sons: the name of the one was Peleg, for in his days the earth was divided, and his brother's name was Joktan.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.10.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 10:26",
      "text": "Joktan became the father of Almodad, Sheleph, Hazarmaveth, Jerah,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.10.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 10:27",
      "text": "Hadoram, Uzal, Diklah,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.10.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 10:28",
      "text": "Obal, Abima-el, Sheba,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.10.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 10:29",
      "text": "Ophir, Havilah, and Jobab; all these were the sons of Joktan.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.10.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 10:30",
      "text": "The territory in which they lived extended from Mesha in the direction of Sephar to the hill country of the east.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.10.31",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 10:31",
      "text": "These are the sons of Shem, by their families, their languages, their lands, and their nations.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:genesis.10.32",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "genesis",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Genesis 10:32",
      "text": "These are the families of the sons of Noah, according to their genealogies, in their nations; and from these the nations spread abroad on the earth after the flood.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
